    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>124400</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_νος"><seg part="F">νος</seg></name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_αστος" type="patronymic"><seg part="F">άστω</seg></name></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέ</supplied>θηκε</w>	 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos (ou <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">fils de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>n)
                (<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>?) <supplied reason="lost">fils de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>astos
                a consacré.
            </p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos (or <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">son of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>n)
                (<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>?) <supplied reason="lost">son of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>astos
                dedicated.</p>
                </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos (o <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">figlio di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>n)
                (<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>?) <supplied reason="lost">figlio di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>astos
                ha dedicato.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Two types of restoration may be suggested:
               1. one name at the accusative and father's name at line 1, one name at the nominative and father's name at line 2, forming the dedication of the statue of 
               the former by the latter; the space available would allow for the formula <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάταν ἀνέθηκε</foreign>;
               2. one name at the nominative at line 1, his father's name at the genitive at line 2, forming an ordinary dedication by one single man and only the verb at line 3.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
